<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Talura cwn'Zeylon:
[B]I wouldn't know about Kerra Ridge. The only time I've been there was to kill off Maugrim. Pretty much everything was green then (pre-update, about 30-32 level). But most Erudites never hang around Odus that long...as I said, they turn in their newbie note, get their robe/shirt, and pound pavement headed to the boat and greener pastures. Would this be the case if the island were equally as developed as Faydwer? Probably not, IMO. It would probably draw some more people to the area if they added in an Odus version of Solusek's Eye or Runnyeye and Splitpaw or Nagafen's Lair.

As to the number of dungeons, there are quite a few that still go unused. Mistmoore, on Drinal, has been pretty much a ghost town when I've been (on Tunare, pre-move, it was a pretty busy place). Sol A, Najena, Splitpaw, Permafrost...rarely see more than 6 people in them, most are L50+ item campers. Why? I have no idea. People go where the safety is, and just hit dungeons for items. 
Maybe in a few months they'll "upgrade" warrens like they did to Splitpaw. I hope not, hope they make it go deeper and get tougher.

It sounds like your dislike is based more on them adding more acreage and not enough content. So far as I know, they don't need to do any updates to client-side to add quests (unless they add mobs for it). They may have changed some npc's in town around. Regardless, you should organize the (small) legion of Erudite clerics and paladins and go to whineplay to ask for more quest content for Erudin, that's how your voice will be heard.[/B][/QUOTE]

